As a variable can store values, it will also be assigned a data type. This can affect the operations that have been applied to the variable within a program.

e.g.

total = 10 #interger

total = 10.5 #float

total = True or False #boolean

total = "10.5" #string

Data types cannot be added together unless they are the same
