defining a function using def

calling a function uses the function name then when to end it, add the function name at the end e.g. my_function()

e.g.

def showMessage():
    print("Error")
    print("oops")

showMessage()

Formal parameters act similar to local variables. It can only be accessed within the specific code block.

return statement is used to return the values that have been entered back, similar to a reset. This can be useful for multiple use of a program

Default argument

a default value is a variable which has already been assigned to a value e.g. name = alice, alice is a default value, if there was code which chnages the name to Joe, it will change the value
