Using a command terminal, to open a python file, type: python filename.py

---------------------------------------------
Formal and Actual Parameters

it is a placeholder for input values within a function definititon, allowing functions to work with different values each time they are called

example: def greet(name):
    print("Hello", name)

name is a formal parameter

actual parameter is the specific value passed to the function when it is called

e.g. greet("Alice")

